  "text": "G-CSF is known to accelerate both proliferation and maturation of neutrophil precursors. [CITATION_1] If plasma concentration of proHNPs does reflect myelopoietic activity, we would expect G-CSF administration to increase the release of proHNPs from bone marrow (proliferation) and to shorten PPI (maturation). This was indeed found in the aSCT patients who all received G-CSF from day þ 5.",
